<article>
  <%= link_to product_path(product) do %>
    <%= image_tag product.image.thumb.url , alt: product.name %>
    <h1>
      <span><%= product.name %></span>
      <span><%= humanized_money_with_symbol product.price %></span>
    </h1>
  <% end %>
  <div>
  <%
=begin%>
  It seems like when a partial is passed with an array of objects, it will render each object with the template like how React does.
  So here, we use the local variable product and its .quantity method to do a conditional rendering of the soldout badge
  Or, alternatively, we can use product[:quantity] to access the quantity of the product
<%
=end%>
    <% if product.quantity == 0 %>
      <p class="soldout">Sold Out</p>
    <% end %>
    <%= button_to add_item_cart_path(product_id: product.id), class: 'btn' ,
    method: :post do %>
      <%= fa_icon "shopping-cart", text: 'Add' %> 
    <% end %>
  </div>
</article>
